Closing Statement

ORL-Chat explores a fundamental possibility:

Meaning in communication can emerge from structure, not from time, order, or synchronization.

It is released openly to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation
broader adoption of structure-first communication systems

Conversations, traditionally governed by sequence and timing, may also be understood as processes of structural resolution.

ORL-Chat is offered as a reference model for that shift.
